  "texts": [
    "As shown in the last column of Table 4, for the lightweight traditional recommenders, the inference time of SASRec is about 1 second for each user.",
    "However for LLMs, except that closed-source models cannot accurately obtain inference time due to limitations of the API, the inference time of open-source models takes nearly 10 or more seconds for one prediction, leading to an unacceptable time delay in practical applications.",
    "Observations on the Overall Recommendation Performance of LLMs• In zero-shot scenarios, LLMs have cold-start capabilities, and GPT-4o even surpasses collaborative filtering models.",
    "However, all LLMs are inferior to fully-trained sequential recommendation models.",
    "• The long-chain reasoning capabilities and slow-thinking process of LLMs are optimized for Mathematics and coding tasks, which is not necessarily suitable for the zero-shot recommendation scenario."
